title: Software Quality Assurance (QA) Automation Engineer
description:
**Position Summary:** The QA Automation Engineer automates tests at the user interface (UI) and application programming interface (API) layers for new and existing products, ranging from browsers to mobile apps to APIs. This professional will be relied upon to own, maintain, and expand the wholistic test automation suite, along with keeping current with and implementing best practices. As QA expands automation coverage, this role will collaborate with various business units in conjunction with the QA Manager to learn, document, automate, and maintain their tests. *This role is eligible for hybrid work from home opportunity under the work from home guidelines two days in the office three days WFH per week upon completion of onboarding.*

  


**Essential Functions:**


* Scope and automate web, mobile, desktop, and API tests.
* Utilize Azure DevOps Repos to contribute to and maintain our test automation code repository.
* Document test automation coverage in our test management software.
* Work with various business units to learn, automate, and maintain their tests.
* Demonstrate completed automation to business units and communicate applicable automation coverage.
* Maintain the wholistic test automation suite.
* Maintain test data and users for test automation.
* Investigate and remediate any failing tests.
* Report any application bugs found to appropriate resources for remediation.
* Assist in researching and recommending test automation tools, frameworks, languages, and best practices.
* Support QA efforts on one or more projects, which may require manual testing, as needed.
* Understand and adhere to all bank policies, laws and regulations applicable to their role, complete compliance training and follow internal processes and controls, as required.
* Report all compliance issues, violations of law or regulations in accordance with the steps defined in bank policies.
* Perform other job\\-related duties or special projects as assigned.
* Regular and reliable attendance is an essential function of this position.


**Qualifications:**


* 1\\-2 years experience in software testing or an associate degree in computer science, software engineering or a related field required.
* 1\\-2 years experience with test automation frameworks required, Playwright, Postman and Appium preferred.
* Experience with test and defect management required.
* Working knowledge of SQL required.
* Experience with REST API testing required.
* Experience working with Azure DevOps or similar tools preferred.
* Prior banking experience preferred.
* Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Office products.


**Preferred Talents:**


* Self\\-starter
* Naturally curious
* Adaptable and willing to learn
* Technically skilled
* Personally accountable
* Analytical and detailed
* Effective verbal and written communication skills for both technical and non\\-technical audiences
* Organized


**Working Environment:**



Indoor work not exposed to outdoor elements or hazards.



Sedentary work, occasional lifting and/or carrying up to twenty pounds.



This role is eligible for hybrid work from home opportunity under the work from home guidelines upon completion of onboarding.

* Knowledge of Windows, Mac, and Linux operating systems and kernels
* Excellent interpersonal skills
* Excellent understanding of computer systems, security, network and systems administration, databases and data storage systems, and telecommunications systems

**Miscellaneous:**

* Must be eligible to work in the United States.
* Ability to work from home with minimal direction

The Analyst, Medical Cost Analytics / Utilization Management role will analytics to evaluate scenarios and make predictions on future outcomes to solve highly complex business problems and support decision making. title: Senior Engineer, IoT
description:
**Senior IoT Engineer**

 **Organization Summary**


Lindsay Corporation is a global company, headquartered in Omaha, Nebraska, focused on providing irrigation and infrastructure solutions to meet the needs of a growing population. As one of the world’s leading providers of irrigation and water management, its Zimmatic systems are operating in more than 90 countries. Lindsay Corporation’s infrastructure division offers a wide range of products that aid in roadway maintenance and transportation safety. Since 1955, Lindsay Corporation has been at the forefront of research and development of products and services designed to meet the needs of a constantly evolving world.

 **Position Description**


Lindsay Corporation is hiring a Senior IoT Engineer within its overall technology organization, reporting to the Director, IoT Engineering in Omaha, NE. This important role will be responsible for designing, implementing, and delivering IoT solutions for Lindsay’s various product lines, including new products and feature development. Additionally, this role will also be responsible for performing maintenance on existing products and solutions.

 **Position Details**


This is a full\\-time, salaried position based at our global headquarters in Omaha, NE and includes a highly competitive salary/benefits package. Travel requirements will be minimal (\\<15%), but there may be some travel to various office locations and conferences.

  

Duties \\& Responsibilities

* Design, develop, and implement firmware and embedded software for IoT devices, ensuring high performance, quality, and reliability
* Collaborate with cross\\-functional teams to integrate hardware and software components, focusing on simplicity and reuse of proven design elements
* Utilize your hardware knowledge to contribute to the development of hardware designs and circuits that promote a seamless interaction between firmware and hardware
* Design products with a focus on customer needs, ensuring that manufacturing, testing, support, and installation are considered throughout the development process
* Actively participate in knowledge sharing, contributing to a culture of transparency and collaboration by documenting and distributing product information
* Evaluate workflows and processes, with a focus on practicality and efficiency
* Acts as a subject matter expert, mentoring and leading other engineers, through expertise and knowledge of current products, technologies, and tools
* Leads new product development efforts, working closely with Team Leads and Project Managers to deliver solutions on time and within the functional specifications
* Participates in code reviews, design reviews, or other forms of team quality assurance procedures

 **Preferred Qualifications**

* Bachelor’s or Master’s degree or equivalent experience in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, or related field.
* 8\\+ years of relevant, professional software engineering experience, including 2\\+ years of experience leading the on\\-time delivery of net\\-new embedded IoT engineering projects/solutions
* Strong proficiency in C or C\\+\\+, demonstrating a solid grasp of programming principles and effective coding techniques, with the ability to mentor others
* Robust problem\\-solving skills, with a proactive approach to finding solutions, the ability to learn from doing, personal accountability, and a positive and professional attitude
* Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with a passion for sharing knowledge and working as part of a team.
* Working knowledge of IoT protocols and standards (e.g., MQTT, TLS, 3GPP, TCP, etc.)
* Ability to work in a fast\\-paced, team\\-oriented environment where constant iteration, improvement, and innovation is key to the success of the team
* Solid understanding, experience, and ability to mentor others on the following: IoT device development, communication, and protocols, Git, embedded RTOS/OS, platform development, embedded hardware
* Demonstrated proficiency and experience with the following languages, technologies, and tools is preferred:
	+ C, C\\+\\+
	+ Test equipment (e.g., oscilloscope, DVM, JTAG debuggers)
	+ IoT protocols and standards (e.g., MQTT, TLS, 3GPP, TCP, etc.)
	+ Cellular, Satellite, and ISM communications
	+ Digital interfaces and protocols (e.g., SPI, I2C, RS485, UART)
	+ Embedded operating systems (e.g. RTOS, Linux,)
	+ IoT Security (e.g., PKI, TLS, TPM)
	+ Integrated Development Environments (e.g., Keil, IAR, VS Code)

 **Why Join Us?**

* Be part of a team that values creativity, collaboration, and making a difference
* Work in an environment that encourages fun and innovation while striving for excellence
* Opportunity to contribute to meaningful projects that have a vast and positive impact on the world

title: Data Analyst - Corporate Controller
description:
**Requisition ID:** 175379


**Job Level:** Entry Level


**Home District/Group:** DHO Operations Controller


**Department:** Data Services


**Market:** Corporate Home Office


**Employment Type:** Full Time


**Position Overview**
---------------------



Do you have a passion for analyzing data and using it to solve problems? At Kiewit, we believe in the power of analytics to create exceptional results. The Corporate Controller Group is seeking a Data Analyst. We are looking for someone with a passion for performing data analysis, data mining, and eventually data science in a professional setting. The Operations Controller group is responsible for all corporate financial reporting, and this role is primarily focused on building PowerApps, Python scripts, data sets, and visualizations.

  

  

As a Data Analyst, you will work with business users to understand challenges and build analytical solutions and processes to overcome those challenges. You will also extract, restructure, analyze, and interpret data, while communicating findings and recommendations to the business and leadership.

  

  

At Kiewit, the scale of our operations is huge. Our construction and engineering projects span across the United States, Canada, and Mexico, improving and connecting communities with every initiative. We depend on our high\\-performing operations support professionals — they’re the glue that holds multiple areas of the business together and the catalysts that make things happen. We hire only the most driven people, and we offer them diverse career opportunities, strong leadership and mentorship, rewarding, collaborative work, and responsibility they won’t find anywhere else. We’re always pushing new limits. You can too.


**District Overview**
---------------------



The Corporate Operations Controller group is dedicated to delivering industry\\-leading financial and operational reporting. Our mission is to ensure that our projects and districts have access to high\\-quality, accurate data, coupled with the right level of analysis, precisely when they need it. We are committed to enhancing the quality, consistency, and accuracy of our reports. Additionally, we strive to leverage our data for deeper analytics, providing our executive team with insightful and actionable analyses. Our core functions revolve around reporting accuracy, advanced analytics, and exceptional customer service.


**Location**
------------



This position is based at Kiewit's corporate headquarters in Omaha, NE.


**Responsibilities**
--------------------


* Deliver Best\\-in\\-Class Solutions: Develop analytical solutions by understanding business challenges and leveraging your technical skills and data knowledge. Aim to provide a world\\-class user experience for Kiewit employees through the power of analytics.
* Data Modeling: Access and restructure various data sources to meet stakeholder needs. Be self\\-sufficient and proficient in SQL to optimize data structures.
* Data Visualization: Create high\\-quality, performant, and insightful visualizations that adhere to best practices and meet specific business requirements.
* Data Analysis: Independently perform data analysis, including hypothesis testing, correlation analysis, and data mining. Make strategic recommendations and articulate their business impact.
* Communication and Presentation: Lead requirement\\-gathering conversations, ask insightful questions, and understand stakeholder perspectives. Present analysis results, train stakeholders on decision support tools, and clearly convey how solutions meet business needs.
* Data Collection: Gain a deep understanding of core applications for data collection. Collaborate with stakeholders and product teams to identify current data capture methods and participate in developing future solutions to capture additional necessary data.


**Qualifications**
------------------



An ideal candidate will have:  

* Bachelor’s degree in Analytics, Statistics, Computer Science, or related field
* Interest in leveraging data to solve unique and challenging business problems
* Formal education and superior results in performing data analysis, data mining, statistical analysis, etc.
* 0\\-3 years of related experience
  


Technical Skills  

* Database querying (SQL for MS SQL Server)
* Proficient in Python
* Data Visualization (Tableau, Power BI)
* Knowledge of data lineage and ETL
  


Non\\-Technical Skills  

* Seeking a highly motivated and self\\-driven individual with a strong sense of initiative
* Must possess excellent attention to detail and the ability to manage multiple tasks and projects with minimal supervision
* Adept at problem\\-solving and critical thinking, with a knack for identifying and addressing challenges efficiently
* The candidate should be a quick learner, adaptable, and open to feedback to continuously improve their performance
* Ability to work independently and as a team to meet deadlines, goals and objectives


Other Requirements:


* Regular, reliable attendance
* Work productively and meet deadlines timely
* Communicate and interact effectively and professionally with supervisors, employees, and others individually or in a team environment.
* Perform work safely and effectively. Understand and follow oral and written instructions, including warning signs, equipment use, and other policies.
* Work during normal operating hours to organize and complete work within given deadlines. Work overtime and weekends as required.
* May work at various different locations and conditions may vary.

  




We offer our fulltime staff employees a comprehensive benefits package that’s among the best in our industry, including top\\-tier medical, dental and vision plans covering eligible employees and dependents, voluntary wellness and employee assistance programs, life insurance, disability, retirement plans with matching, and generous paid time off.


We are an Equal Opportunity Employer. Employment decisions are made without regard to race, color, religion, national or ethnic origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, protected veteran status or other characteristics protected by law.

title: Customer Support Systems Engineer
description:
It's not just about your career or job title... It's about who you are and the impact you will make on the world. Because whether it's for each other or our customers, we put People First. **Who will you be working with?** 




 As the
 *Customer Support Systems Engineer, you will be working with the Railroad project manager and its designated contacts, Wabtec technical project manager, design, systems and subsystems engineers and field service engineers. Here you'll interact daily with the customer during the problem resolution process and will partner with other key stakeholders to support our customers and their operations.* 








**How will you make a difference?** 




*As the Customer Support Systems Engineer, you'll lead the effort in identifying the gap between contractual target performance KPI's and actual performance of the product in the field. You'll be responsible for gathering, analyzing, and interpreting large volumes of data to uncover root causes of performance gaps, provide actionable insights, and drive performance improvements.* 








**What do we want to know about you?** 



* *Bachelor's degree in computer or software engineering*
* *Minimum 3\\-5 years of relevant experience*
* *Excellent communication and problem\\-solving skills*
* *Knowledge of Lean Six Sigma and root cause analysis*
* *Ability to drive change and innovation*
* *Experience with development and/or testing of real\\-time embedded systems and C/C\\+\\+ programming in transportation*
* *Planning and Organizing: Plans work effectively, sets priorities, communicates plans, and prepares for potential issues.*
* *Problem Analysis: Collects and organizes information, identifies trends, and makes connections for analysis.*
* *Learning Ability: Applies new knowledge, seeks feedback, and adapts behavior based on latest information.*
* *Written Communication: Writes clear, concise, and reader\\-focused communications.*
* *Teamwork: Works towards collective results, stimulates teamwork, and helps others achieve their goals.*
* *Adaptability: Adjusts activities and behavior in response to changes and proposes effective ways to manage them.*
* *Integrity: Takes responsibility for actions, maintains confidentiality, and is honest about risks and opportunities.*
* *Results Orientation: Sets and achieves ambitious goals, delivers results, and proposes more efficient methods.*







**What will your typical day look like?** 



* *\\- Analyze logs from reported field issues to disposition as known issues or identify new failure modes*
* *\\- Inspect system requirements and subsystem requirements to identify when system behavior in the field is not in compliance*
* *\\- Recreate failures from the field using HITL simulators and/or desktop simulation tools*
* *\\- Generate customer facing documentation for newly identified failure modes including conditions for failure, impact of failure and possible mitigations*
* *\\- Generate internal facing documentation for newly identified failure modes to feed to the engineering team for resolution*
* *\\- Drive the development of automated systems for measuring and reporting system KPI performance*
* *\\- Drive development of tools and systems for automated identification of known failure modes in system logs*
* *\\- Drive development of tools for increased productivity in recreating failure modes from the field"*







 You may also be asked to perform other duties outside of your function or trade, for which adequate training will be provided if necessary.
 







**Preferred location Omaha, NE. Other locations will be considered.** 








 More information on offered benefits, which include health, welfare, and retirement, is available at mywabtecbenefits.com.
 







 Relocation assistance may be provided if eligibility requirements are met.
 







 Wabtec will only employ those who are legally authorized to work in the U.S. for this opening. Any offer of employment is conditioned upon the successful completion of a drug screen (as applicable) and fitness for duty test (as applicable).
 











 Our job titles may span more than one career level. The salary range for this role is between
 


 $77,400\\.00\\-$110,300\\.00
 




 The actual salary offered to a candidate may be influenced by a variety of factors, such as: training, transferable skills, work experience, education, business needs, market demands and work location. The base pay range is subject to change and may be modified in the future. More information on offered benefits, which include health, welfare, and retirement, are available at mywabtecbenefits.com. Other benefit offerings for this role may include an annual bonus, if eligible.
 







**Who are we?** 















 Wabtec Corporation is a leading global provider of equipment, systems, digital solutions, and value\\-added services for freight and transit rail as well as the mining, marine, and industrial markets. Drawing on nearly four centuries of collective experience across Wabtec, GE Transportation, and Faiveley Transport, the company has grown to become One Wabtec, with unmatched digital expertise, technological innovation, and world\\-class manufacturing and services, enabling the digital\\-rail\\-and\\-transit ecosystems.
 







 Wabtec is focused on performance that drives progress and unlocks our customers' potential by delivering innovative and lasting transportation solutions that move and improve the world. We are lifelong learners obsessed with making things better to drive exceptional results. Wabtec has approximately 27K employees in facilities throughout the world. Visit our website to learn more! http://www.WabtecCorp.com
 







**Our Commitment to Embrace Diversity:** 




 Wabtec is a global company that invests not just in our products, but also our people by embracing diversity and inclusion. We care about our relationships with our employees and take pride in celebrating the variety of experiences, expertise, and backgrounds that bring us together. At Wabtec, we aspire to create a place where we all belong and where diversity is welcomed and appreciated.
 







 To fulfill that commitment, we rely on a culture of leadership, diversity, and inclusion. We aim to employ the world's brightest minds to help us create a limitless source of ideas and opportunities. We have created a space where everyone is given the opportunity to contribute based on their individual experiences and perspectives and recognize that these differences and diverse perspectives make us better.
 







 We believe in hiring talented people of varied backgrounds, experiences, and styles... People like you! Wabtec Corporation is committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or expression, or protected Veteran status. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know.

title: Data, Reporting & Analytics Program Cutover Lead
description:
MatchPoint Solutions is a fast\\-growing, young, energetic global IT\\-Engineering services company with clients across the US. We provide technology solutions to various clients like Uber, Robinhood, Netflix, Airbnb, Google, Sephora, and more! More recently, we have expanded to working internationally in Canada, China, Ireland, UK, Brazil, and India. Through our culture of innovation, we inspire, build, and deliver business results, from idea to outcome. We keep our clients on the cutting edge of the latest technologies and provide solutions by using industry\\-specific best practices and expertise.
 



 We are excited to be continuously expanding our team. If you are interested in this position, please send over your updated resume. We look forward to hearing from you!
 



**Data, Reporting \\& Analytics Program Cutover Lead** 




**Onsite \\- Omaha, NE** 




**6\\+ Months** 




**$55 \\- $60/hr on W2** 




**Summary** 




 We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Cutover Lead to oversee and manage the transition of critical technology solutions associated with the ERP Data, Reporting \\& Analytics Program. This effort is part of an overall SAP ECC to SAP S/4HANA upgrade and is focused solely on the downstream data implications to client's analytic environments. The scope of this position includes the definition of a detailed migration plan associated downstream data warehouse platforms and analytic solutions and partnering with other cross\\-initiative efforts to ensure one, cohesive, and accurate workplan is created and implemented. This individual will ensure seamless integration and minimal disruption to business operations while implementing new technology solutions. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience in managing technical processes, coordinating with cross\\-functional teams, and ensuring the integrity and accuracy of data throughout the migration process. This role requires a strong understanding of the sequence and dependencies between SAP, data pipelines, data analytic environments, and various consumption and reporting technologies. The successful candidate will ensure the integrity, accuracy, and reliability of data throughout the migration processes.
 



**Primary Responsibilities** 



* Plan and lead the execution of system cutover activities during SAP upgrade for the data warehouse platforms and related deployment of analytical solutions
* Develop and implement cutover strategies and detailed plans, with a strong focus on minimal business disruption balanced with technical performance
* Gather and document appropriate cutover activities with project managers, technical teams, and business stakeholders to ensure alignment and readiness
* Oversee data migration tasks, ensure timely completion of all required activities
* Identify and mitigate potential risks and issues related to system cutovers, data migrations, and analytic solution deployments
* Collaborate with cross\\-functional teams to facilitate effective and timely communication
* Monitor and report on the progress of cutover activities, providing regular updates to program and initiative leadership
* Conduct post\\-cutover reviews and provide recommendations for future improvements, particularly in the context of data pipelines and analytic solutions



**Qualifications** 



* Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field
* Proven experience in leading data warehouse migrations and deployment of analytic solutions.
* Strong understanding of technical processes and best practices for system cutovers, with a focus on downstream data solutions
* Experience with data integrity, data accuracy, and data completeness during migration activities, particularly in building data pipelines
* Excellent project management and organizational skills
* Strong problem\\-solving abilities and attention to detail
* Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross\\-functional teams
* Ability to anticipate and mitigate risks related to system cutovers, data migrations, and analytic solution deployments
* Familiarity with analytic solutions, business intelligence tools, and citizen developer reports and applications

title: Senior Systems Administrator
description:
The Senior Systems Administrator works within the framework of established operating procedures and in close cooperation with internal and external support personnel; takes a lead role in the planning, development, implementation, maintenance and support of the Health System's server infrastructure to assure operational availability. Responsible for all phases of MS Windows Servers/Clusters, VMWare environment, Citrix environment, VDI environment, MS SQL environment, MS Exchange Server as well as physical servers, blade servers/environments, backup systems and storage solutions of all Intel\\-based systems
 



  
 



 PRINCIPAL JOB FUNCTIONS:
 



 1\\. \\*Commits to the mission, vision, beliefs and consistently demonstrates our core values.
 



 2\\. \\*Maintains, administers and installs servers, including but not limited to, installation and configuration of new and existing servers, server upgrades; creates and maintains accurate server and project related documentation.
 



 3\\. \\*Maintains and creates backup solutions for servers; provides maintenance, backup and recovery plans for servers and database systems.
 



 4\\. Maintains and deploys anti\\-virus and anti\\-spyware protection for the Medical Center.
 



 5\\. \\*Designs, maintains and administers user and server security; designs workstation security and works with IT support staff on implementation and administration.
 



 6\\. \\*Creates, tests and deploys software packages and scripts to install, update and maintain software packages on workstations.
 



 7\\. Researches specifications and makes recommendations of servers, capacity of servers, server\\-related hardware devices and software.
 



 8\\. Effectively uses project management tools and methodologies.
 



 9\\. \\*Serves as a project leader on diverse Medical Center\\-wide projects in order to ensure that technology implementation is effective; coaches other staff on issues related to system administration.
 



 10\\. Works with departmental staff to create processes and standards to deploy new technologies.
 



 11\\. \\*Develops, coordinates and implements schedules with vendor and users of applications to achieve a successful implementation process; works with vendors to troubleshoot and solve complex technical problems including network, server, printing, management tools, operating systems, etc.
 



 12\\. Assists in the testing and documentation of new and updated software to ensure quality control and performance standards are met.
 



 13\\. Provides ongoing second level support of installed systems and end\\-user hardware/software issues.
 



 14\\. \\*Provides regular feedback to management regarding system administration issues; advises management of new developments in hardware, software, systems administration, systems optimization and systems management.
 



 15\\. Enters restricted access areas, without supervision, to perform assigned work.
 



 16\\. Performs other related duties as assigned.
 



 (Essential Job functions are marked with an asterisk “\\*”. Refer to the Guide for the definition of essential and non\\-essential job functions.) Attach Addendum for positions with slightly different roles or work\\-specific differences as needed.
 



  
 



 REQUIRED KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES:
 



 1\\. Knowledge of Active Directory design, deployment, maintenance and group policy management.
 



 2\\. Knowledge of Windows servers design, configuration and implementation.
 



 3\\. Knowledge of Terminal server technologies including Citrix Metaframe/Presentation server, MS Virtual server and VMware.
 



 4\\. Knowledge of Microsoft SQL Server administration, MS Windows and MS Office, Linux, MS Project and enterprise backup solutions.
 



 5\\. Knowledge of enterprise storage systems, SAN, NAS, iSCSI.
 



 6\\. Knowledge of server class hardware and blade systems.
 



 7\\. Knowledge of network design, IP protocol suite and network devices.
 



 8\\. Knowledge of PC configurations and troubleshooting MS Windows workstations.
 



 9\\. Knowledge of VPN technologies.
 



 10\\. Knowledge of scripting or light programming as it relates to workstations and server task automation.
 



 11\\. Skill in the core competencies with respect to design, implementation and team leadership.
 



 12\\. Ability to identify and evaluate alternative and innovative solutions to problems.
 



 13\\. Ability to create appropriate network and systems documentation.
 



 14\\. Ability to establish and manage priorities, plan multiple and complex tasks and evaluate outcomes.
 



 15\\. Ability to communicate effectively both orally and in writing.
 



 16\\. Ability to lead teams and work as a team member.
 



 17\\. Ability to interact effectively with clients, coworkers and vendors having a broad range of computer knowledge and ability.
 



 18\\. Ability to grasp complex technical and business systems, processes and principles across IT functions and relationships in support of organizational goals.
 



  
 



 EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE:
 



 Associate’s Degree in Computer Science or equivalent field of study required. Bachelors of Science Degree in Computer Science or equivalent field of study preferred. Microsoft certification required. Minimum of four (4\\) years experience implementing, testing and troubleshooting in a complex Microsoft Windows environment required. Linux experience preferred.
 



  
 



 OTHER CREDENTIALS / CERTIFICATIONS:
 



 Maintains skill sets and certifications for the core competencies of MS Servers, VMWare \\& Citrix.
 



  
 



 PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:
 



 (Physical Requirements are based on federal criteria and assigned by Human Resources upon review of the Principal Job Functions.)
 



 (DOT) – Characterized as sedentary work requiring exertion up to 10 pounds of force occasionally and/or a negligible amount of force frequently to lift, carry, push, pull, or otherwise move objects, including the human body.
 



 Sedentary work involves sitting most of the time, but may involve walking or standing for brief periods of time.

title: Purchasing Coordinator - 82k Salary
description:
**Purchasing Coordinator – 87,000 Salary – 15% annual bonus of Salary** 




**Position:** 
  Purchasing Coordinator
 



**Salary:** 
  $65,000 to $87,000 per year (Based on experience)
 



**Location:** 
  Omaha, NE
 



**Job Description:** 
  As a Purchasing Coordinator, you will be responsible for managing the procurement process for a diverse range of materials and supplies critical to the production of our precast concrete products. This role requires strong organizational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to work effectively with suppliers and internal teams to ensure timely and cost\\-effective procurement.
 



**Essential Duties and Job Responsibilities:** 



* Purchase a variety of materials necessary for precast concrete production, including but not limited to: Cement, Aggregates, Admixtures, Reinforcing Materials, Formwork Materials, Sealing and Curing Compounds, Miscellaneous Supplies.
* Identify, evaluate, and select suppliers based on cost, quality, and delivery time.
* Establish and maintain strong relationships with suppliers to negotiate favorable terms and resolve any issues related to delivery or quality.
* Monitor supplier performance and ensure compliance with contractual obligations.
* Create and manage purchase orders, ensuring accuracy and completeness.
* Coordinate with the inventory team to maintain optimal stock levels and prevent shortages.
* Analyze market trends and pricing to identify cost\\-saving opportunities.
* Conduct regular price comparisons and negotiate contracts to achieve the best possible pricing for materials.
* Maintain accurate records of purchase orders, supplier agreements, and inventory levels.
* Prepare regular reports on purchasing activities, inventory status, and cost analyses.
* Work closely with production, engineering, and quality control teams to understand material requirements and resolve any supply\\-related issues.
* Participate in cross\\-functional meetings to provide insights and updates on procurement activities.



**Qualification Requirements:** 







1. **Education:** 
  Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain Management, Business Administration, Construction Management, or a related field preferred.
2. **Experience:** 
  Minimum of 3 years of experience in purchasing or procurement, preferably in a manufacturing or construction environment.
3. **Skills:**


+ Strong negotiation and communication skills.
+ Proficiency in procurement software and Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Word, Outlook).
+ Ability to analyze data, manage multiple priorities, and work under pressure.
+ Knowledge of materials used in precast concrete manufacturing is a significant advantage.


1. **Technical/Mathematical Skills:**


+ Ability to perform addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
+ Ability to calculate area and volume.
+ Ability to apply concepts of basic geometry.


1. **Reasoning Ability:**


+ Ability to define problems, collect data, establish facts, and draw valid conclusions.
+ Ability to interpret a variety of technical instructions in mathematical or diagram form.


1. **Physical Demands:**

+ While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to walk, climb, sit, use hands to finger, handle or feel objects, tools, or controls; and talk and hear. Manual lifting requirements are moderate to heavy, but with the assistance of other personnel and cranes.







**Employee Value Proposition (EVP):**

The work described will require the Purchasing Coordinator to be in the plant the majority of the time.
